posts.title: I cannot understand the AWFUL mindset that trusts government.
posts.content:
Affluent White Feminist Urban Liberal.

Maybe it's because I'm blue collar. Maybe because I'm only 1 generation from my family living in abject poverty as tenant farmers. Maybe it's because both sides of my family are from the traditional antebellum south. Maybe it's because I grew up in Texas who's bone deep distrust in government lead the writers of our post reconstruction constitution to enshrine so many restrictions on government and only allowing the legislature to be in session 150 days every 2 years.

But, I simply do not trust any government. It doesn't matter which level. Be it local, to state, to federal, to world. I assume any government to be at best indifferent to my needs and more often hostile to them. Nothing I have seen from any government anywhere at any time gives me reason to think otherwise. Every government ever is destructive and exploitative of its citizens rights, property, and lives. More often these same AWFUL people will complain about government themselves in one breath then turn arround and place all responsibility for their lifes decisions in the hands of the very same government.
